keyValuePair.Value: Does defeat today damage the team's confidence?
It always seemed like a difficult game today between two pretty evenly-matched teams. Did you think your boys looked a little short on self-belief? Is that why you lost?
Maybe we just lacked a bit of self-belief.

It's a disappointing result and maybe confidence was an issue. But to overcome that you need to focus on the positives. I have to say I thought the players gave everything and didn't really deserve to lose. We'll get back on the training pitch and work hard before our next game.
One mistake can be costly, can't it?

I've been impressed with our defending recently so I don't know why confidence would be an issue. I thought we looked pretty solid most of the game today, too. But one mistake cost us the points and that's something the lads will have to put right next week. We can't afford those kinds of slip-ups.
Confidence is such a big part of the game.

I think we're a decent team. But today was disappointing. We never really looked ourselves. We hurried things, we made poor decisions with the final ball. I'm not sure why the players would be lacking in confidence. I believe in them. Maybe it's my job to make them believe in themselves.
What do you think went wrong today?
That was a very tough game for you. And a very disappointing result. You don't look happy at all. Where do you think it went wrong for the team today?
Look, you can't win every week.
Look, you can't win every week.

Of course I'm disappointed. I thought there wasn't really that much between the two teams today. Sometimes you just have to recognise that it's not been your day. You can't win every game. Although, as a manager, of course I wish we could!

Of course I'm disappointed. I thought there wasn't really that much between the two teams today. Sometimes you just have to recognise that it's not been your day. You can't win every game. Although, as a manager, of course I wish we could!
We needed a goal when it mattered.

In a fixture like that, you need to score when you're having a spell on top. If we could have got just one goal at the right time, I think the outcome could have been very different. I guess we just need to find a little more in the final third if we want to win games like today's.

In a fixture like that, you need to score when you're having a spell on top. If we could have got just one goal at the right time, I think the outcome could have been very different. I guess we just need to find a little more in the final third if we want to win games like today's.
We have to make sure we keep our heads.
We have to make sure we keep our heads.

We've turned in some decent defensive performances recently. But today? Once we conceded the first goal, we seemed to lose our shape and our discipline. We forgot our good habits. But we'll be fine. We know we can do better. We have to get back to doing the simple things well.
It's hard to say, really. Our approach was generally good and the boys played well. We were unlucky to end up two behind and it's difficult to get back in the game from there.
A tough game for you. Could you have done anything different?
It was always going to be a tough game against an in-form team. But are you disappointed with your team's performance? Could things have been different?
We didn't create enough chances.
We didn't create enough chances.

If I'm looking for a positive from today, I thought we worked really hard to get into the game. But the shape of the team wasn't right and we didn't create enough good chances. I take my share of responsibility for that. It's been a frustrating day.

If I'm looking for a positive from today, I thought we worked really hard to get into the game. But the shape of the team wasn't right and we didn't create enough good chances. I take my share of responsibility for that. It's been a frustrating day.
We've got work to do, haven't we?
We've got work to do, haven't we?

I don't feel like being too harsh on the boys. They worked hard. Things didn't go their way. But, in the end, you've just got to put your hands up and admit we were second best. We're all going to need to stick together and put the hours in on the training ground if we're going to compete against teams as good as that.
We didn't defend well when it really mattered.

I don't want to be too quick to judge and, of course, I'll watch the game back tonight. But it seemed to me that the difference between the two teams today really was about concentration and discipline as much as anything. That means looking at our defensive work. I have to ask why we weren't able to make the right decisions at the key moments and keep a clean sheet.

I don't want to be too quick to judge and, of course, I'll watch the game back tonight. But it seemed to me that the difference between the two teams today really was about concentration and discipline as much as anything. That means looking at our defensive work. I have to ask why we weren't able to make the right decisions at the key moments and keep a clean sheet.
That can't have been much fun to watch as a manager. What went wrong?
%1s are a very good team and so getting a result today was always going to be difficult. But you must be disappointed with how the game went. What went wrong for your team?
We didn't deal with their pressing.

I think we struggled against their pressing game. I don't want to be over-critical of my players because they worked as hard as they could. I just hope they'll learn lessons from playing against opponents as good as the ones they were up against today.
They put us under a lot of pressure.

I can't really be too critical of the players. We were up against a better team today. %1s are as good as anyone at the moment. They're in great form and we just couldn't get hold of the ball for long enough at a time to really compete.
We didn't cause them enough problems.

We always knew we were going to be without the ball for long spells today. In this kind of game, you need to defend from the front and make it difficult for the opponents to get into their rhythm. We weren't good at the closing down part of the job today and I'm disappointed by that. We have to learn to be harder to play against when we face teams that are better than us.
What did you make of today's defeat? You must be disappointed?
Taking form and league position into account, you must be disappointed with today's result. What went wrong for your team?
%1s were just better than us on the day.

You know what they say: you win or you learn. Whatever anybody predicted, %1s were better than us today. We just have to go back to work, take the lessons from this defeat and do what we need to do to improve.

You know what they say: you win or you learn. Whatever anybody predicted, %1s were better than us today. We just have to go back to work, take the lessons from this defeat and do what we need to do to improve.
Our defending wasn't good enough.

We worked on defending set plays all week. We worked on a plan to nullify the opposition. We give the lads all the information they needed. But, once the game kicks off, it's up to them. Today all the good work we'd done on the training ground was forgotten about, it seemed. Our defending was nowhere near good enough.

We worked on defending set plays all week. We worked on a plan to nullify the opposition. We give the lads all the information they needed. But, once the game kicks off, it's up to them. Today all the good work we'd done on the training ground was forgotten about, it seemed. Our defending was nowhere near good enough.
We just couldn't get enough of the ball.

I know we've got some very good attacking players. I watch them in training every week. But, today, it was as if we couldn't ever get started. I need the lads to start games more aggressively. We need to impose ourselves. And, of course, we need to score goals. We've got to be better than we were today, that's for sure.

I know we've got some very good attacking players. I watch them in training every week. But, today, it was as if we couldn't ever get started. I need the lads to start games more aggressively. We need to impose ourselves. And, of course, we need to score goals. We've got to be better than we were today, that's for sure.
A very frustrating day for you. What went wrong?
A bit of a surprise result today and it must leave you feeling frustrated. What went wrong? And what will you say to your players?
We didn't create enough going forward.

A game like that, I feel sorry for the boys up front, really. They were getting in good positions but the ball never came to them. We should have worked harder to make things happen, tried to win the ball back higher up the pitch. The boys grafted but they know they can be better than that.

A game like that, I feel sorry for the boys up front, really. They were getting in good positions but the ball never came to them. We should have worked harder to make things happen, tried to win the ball back higher up the pitch. The boys grafted but they know they can be better than that.
We got surprised by their line-up.

I've got to admit we were surprised by their team shape today. My boys got a bit outnumbered in key areas and we paid the price. The lads did what they could and perhaps I should have changed things earlier, but I was hoping we'd be able to cope. It just didn't work out.

I've got to admit we were surprised by their team shape today. My boys got a bit outnumbered in key areas and we paid the price. The lads did what they could and perhaps I should have changed things earlier, but I was hoping we'd be able to cope. It just didn't work out.
We've got to communicate better.

Man for man, I wouldn't swap my players for anybody else's. But we got caught out today, didn't we? We had a plan for dealing with them but we didn't work together as a unit at all. Everybody was off doing their own thing. Where was the talking? We have to communicate better.
Do you think the score was a fair reflection of the game?
It's always tough to lose to a rival, especially when it's by such a narrow margin. Do you think the scoreline was a fair reflection of how the game went?
Games like this get settled by really fine margins.

I thought we mostly did okay today. We worked hard enough. But it's tough. Games like this get settled by really fine margins. One goal between the teams and it could just have easily gone our way, I think.
They took their chance. We didn't.

I can't criticise my players for effort but you saw what a tight game it was. It's all about fine margins. We didn't take chances at the vital moments. Our rivals did. And that was the difference. We need to work on our decision-making.
There wasn't much between the teams.

I can't fault my lads for effort. That was a very tight game and I think it could have gone either way. Just the one goal separating us. I could easily have been standing here talking to you about how we won. We just have to be better in the key moments, don't we?

I can't fault my lads for effort. That was a very tight game and I think it could have gone either way. Just the one goal separating us. I could easily have been standing here talking to you about how we won. We just have to be better in the key moments, don't we?
That was a crushing defeat. Will it damage your team's confidence?
Not a good result and made worse by the fact that it was against %1s. Is it going to be difficult to lift the spirits of your players after that kind of defeat?
Maybe we lacked a bit of self-belief.

Confidence is a funny thing, isn't it? I definitely hope the lads won't struggle after today. We worked very hard for each other but just didn't create enough chances to make a proper game of it. I want them all to keep their chins up, though.
The lads won't need me to tell them what went wrong.

Look, we're all professionals here and there's no point feeling sorry for ourselves. I won't need to explain anything to my players. They already know they didn't do themselves justice today. The challenge now is for them to improve next time out.

Look, we're all professionals here and there's no point feeling sorry for ourselves. I won't need to explain anything to my players. They already know they didn't do themselves justice today. The challenge now is for them to improve next time out.
We weren't strong enough physically.
We weren't strong enough physically.

We had a plan but we didn't stick to it. In games against your rivals, you have to win the individual battles and we just didn't do that today. We got bullied and that's not what I expect from my players. I'm sure I'll see improvement next time out, though, that's for sure.
